  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Graves' disease is characterized by thyrotoxicosis, goiter, ophthalmopathy and dermopathy.
      Pathogenesis involves autoimmune process. The investigators think temperatures of the area
      involved in the inflammation may change. Thus the investigators plan to take temperature
      pictures of Graves' patients using digital infrared thermal imaging system and observe the
      change.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      We will recruited patients of Graves' disease from out patient clinics. We will perform
      thyroid echo and soft tissue echo first. Then we let patients sit before the thermal camera
      and take thermal images of eyes necks and tibia. After data collection, we analyse the
      relation between temperature and laboratory data such as thyroid function and autoimmune
      profiles.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
